Package com.electronicAssetTrading

  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    AccountSettings
    Account Settings pages gives the user an overview of the all the assets their organisation owns Additionally, the user can change their password, and if the user is an admin they are able to add an asset to their organisation
    AddAsset
    AddAsset the page where an admin is able to add a new asset to the database
    AssetPreview
    The main purpose is to produce a confirmation page, allow the users to verify their buy or selling option before confirming the transaction.
    Assets
    This classâ€™s job is to generate a GUI that display a list of all available assets that are currently up for transaction.
    ChangePassword
    Change Password as the name implies is the page where a user will change their password this password is stored as a hash in the database
    ConnectToDb
    The first page that is built to run and then use the Electronic Asset Trading application here the user connects to the database inserting the server address, port number and credentials to the database.
    Login
    The login page give the user access to the application if their user details are in the database
    TradeConfirmation
    Trade confirmation is the page that shows a user the asset they have successfully traded
    Trades
    Trades is the page where a user can see all the trades that have been processed over a period of time
